<div id="review_315957716" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/315957716" />
    <a title="Julie " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5210022-julie"><img alt="Julie " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1356906542p2/5210022.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/315957716?book_show_action=true">Apr 20, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julie " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julie " href="/user/show/5210022-julie">Julie </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer315957716" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer614023874596709743">This one was more like the Linda Howard I was used to. She did a good job of making you see the down side of winning the lottery. We saw the hassle of it and how friends can turn on you quite suddenly in those circumstances.<br/>Once we have all that established, the mystery, suspense develops. Some of it was silly. I don&apos;t think a citizen, even if they were in extreme danger would have been handcuffed and held hostage against their will. But, the romance had to develop somehow I suppose. There were </span>
  <span id="freeText614023874596709743" style="display:none">This one was more like the Linda Howard I was used to. She did a good job of making you see the down side of winning the lottery. We saw the hassle of it and how friends can turn on you quite suddenly in those circumstances.<br />Once we have all that established, the mystery, suspense develops. Some of it was silly. I don't think a citizen, even if they were in extreme danger would have been handcuffed and held hostage against their will. But, the romance had to develop somehow I suppose. There were some sad moments toward the climax of the book, but it's not too dark or heavy. But, there's a happy ending. As fast read, and typical of Howard's other romantic suspense novels. This was best one of her's I have read in a while.</span>
  <a data-text-id="614023874596709743" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


