    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_73046366" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/73046366" />
    <a title="Holly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1881626-holly"><img alt="Holly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1231395381p2/1881626.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/73046366?book_show_action=true">Sep 30, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Holly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Holly" href="/user/show/1881626-holly">Holly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1881626-holly?shelf=read-in-2009">read-in-2009</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1881626-holly?shelf=september-2009">september-2009</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer73046366" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10178725403548160640">I&apos;ve been disappointed in most of LH&apos;s more recent releases, but I was pleasantly surprised with this one. It reminded me quite a bit of All the Queen&apos;s Men. Kind of light on the romance and heavy on the storyline, but still oddly satisfying.<br/><br/>I was concerned that the resolution between Jenner and Cael wouldn&apos;t be quite satisfactory, but I was pleased with the way it turned out. I felt we got to know both characters and they worked well together.<br/><br/>The storyline was interesting b/c it took place almo</span>
  <span id="freeText10178725403548160640" style="display:none">I've been disappointed in most of LH's more recent releases, but I was pleasantly surprised with this one. It reminded me quite a bit of All the Queen's Men. Kind of light on the romance and heavy on the storyline, but still oddly satisfying.<br /><br />I was concerned that the resolution between Jenner and Cael wouldn't be quite satisfactory, but I was pleased with the way it turned out. I felt we got to know both characters and they worked well together.<br /><br />The storyline was interesting b/c it took place almost exclusively on a cruise ship. The suspense plot didn't contain much mystery - the villain was introduced almost immediately - but it still worked. I'm sure if I thought long enough I could find plenty of holes in the story, but the truth is I was entertained enough that I didn't care. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10178725403548160640" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

