        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer269949351" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15231974438860695523">Didn&apos;t like this one much - too implausible (yeah,I know...it&apos;s a romance!!!) and the pacing was weird - too much detail in some places and not enough in others. The author mentioned the heroine&apos;s &quot;small but perky breasts&quot; way too often, and testicles, she mentioned testicles a few too many times (it&apos;s such a weird word, I think once per book is enough, or none per book would be better.) I listened to this one and that&apos;s another problem. The woman who read the audio just dropped her voice down a</span>
  <span id="freeText15231974438860695523" style="display:none">Didn't like this one much - too implausible (yeah,I know...it's a romance!!!) and the pacing was weird - too much detail in some places and not enough in others. The author mentioned the heroine's "small but perky breasts" way too often, and testicles, she mentioned testicles a few too many times (it's such a weird word, I think once per book is enough, or none per book would be better.) I listened to this one and that's another problem. The woman who read the audio just dropped her voice down an octave when reading the male dialogue - and she still sounded too much like a woman imitating a man - don't know what the solution to this should be but there needs to be one...it's just not sexy.</span>
