<div id="review_553633035" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/553633035" />
    <a title="Taryn Elliott" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3987585-taryn-elliott"><img alt="Taryn Elliott" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1464412575p2/3987585.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/553633035?book_show_action=true">Mar 06, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Taryn Elliott" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Taryn Elliott" href="/user/show/3987585-taryn-elliott">Taryn Elliott</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3987585-taryn-elliott?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3987585-taryn-elliott?shelf=snarky">snarky</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer553633035" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2287334780101090024">I&apos;ve been a Linda Howard fan girl for a long time, but man...Jenner really tipped the scales on the annoying factor for me. The story was great, the mystery and the villain was awesome, but I just couldn&apos;t get past the constant repetition from Jenner&apos;s character about her trust issues and that she had to have some level of control over her &apos;kidnapper&apos;. <br/><br/>Don&apos;t get me wrong.<br/>The book had areas where she should be mistrustful of our Hero--and I get that. I didn&apos;t want her to fall head over ass for hi</span>
  <span id="freeText2287334780101090024" style="display:none">I've been a Linda Howard fan girl for a long time, but man...Jenner really tipped the scales on the annoying factor for me. The story was great, the mystery and the villain was awesome, but I just couldn't get past the constant repetition from Jenner's character about her trust issues and that she had to have some level of control over her 'kidnapper'. <br /><br />Don't get me wrong.<br />The book had areas where she should be mistrustful of our Hero--and I get that. I didn't want her to fall head over ass for him easily, but OMG. Shrill bitchery is not funny snark. And believe me. I love snark.<br /><br />It was redeemed in the end, but dealing with 1/3 of the book and the screeching? I couldn't give it better than 3 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2287334780101090024" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


